# OpenClaw Traefik Routing Contract

All new app containers must follow this routing pattern.

## Required Defaults

- Reverse proxy is Traefik.
- Docker network: `{{ openclaw_policy_network_name }}`.
- Router entrypoint: `{{ openclaw_policy_entrypoint }}`.
- TLS required: `{{ openclaw_policy_require_tls | bool }}`.

## Required Compose Pattern

Use this shape for every app container:

```yaml
services:
  <app_name>:
    image: <image>
    networks:
      - {{ openclaw_policy_network_name }}
    labels:
      - "traefik.enable=true"
      - "traefik.docker.network={{ openclaw_policy_network_name }}"
      - "traefik.http.routers.<app_name>.rule=Host(`<app_name>.{{ openclaw_policy_domain | default('<domain>', true) }}`)"
      - "traefik.http.routers.<app_name>.entrypoints={{ openclaw_policy_entrypoint }}"
{% if openclaw_policy_require_tls | bool %}
      - "traefik.http.routers.<app_name>.tls=true"
{% endif %}
      - "traefik.http.services.<app_name>.loadbalancer.server.port=<internal_port>"

networks:
  {{ openclaw_policy_network_name }}:
    external: true
```

## Guardrails

- Do not expose app ports on the host (`ports:`) unless explicitly requested.
- Always keep `traefik.http.services.<app>.loadbalancer.server.port` set to the app internal port.
- Keep wildcard subdomain model `<app>.{{ openclaw_policy_domain | default('<domain>', true) }}` unless explicitly overridden.
